OL,7,FOn Sunday January 4, the coldest
OL,8,Ftemperature in the UK was recorded in
OL,9,FShap, at -10.9C.
OL,11,FThe MET Office anticipates the rest of
OL,12,Fthe week to be less cold, with lows of
OL,13,F-3C forecast in Hawick on Friday 9
OL,14,FJanuary, while Carlisle might see a
OL,15,Flow of -4C.
OL,17,FThe MET Office explained the cold and
OL,18,Fice is due to 'an Artic airmass
OL,19,Fcovering the UK'.
OL,21,FHow have hospitals been affected?
